<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4838] add unix domain socket support to Swift TSocketTransport implementation </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4838</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TSocketTransport in Objective-C supports initWithPath: for unix domain sockets:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/f3ec277e7e2c147342831ecec590bc2f71b07761/lib/cocoa/src/transport/TSocketTransport.m#L82&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/f3ec277e7e2c147342831ecec590bc2f71b07761/lib/cocoa/src/transport/TSocketTransport.m#L82&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However since the Objective-C implementation has been removed in 0.13, the Swift version does not implement this:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/lib/swift/Sources/TSocketTransport.swift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/lib/swift/Sources/TSocketTransport.swift&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before this is done I think TCFSocketTransport should be moved to its own file. This would avoid extra #if logic to prevent Linux compiling, and simplify the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
